               <floruit notBefore="1696" notAfter="1712">He was a dignitary at 
                  the court of 
                  <persName ref="PRS5616IyasuI"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName>
                     ʾIyāsu the Great</persName> during the period between <date>1696-1712</date>. 
                  He belonged to the royal army, fulfilling the function of <persName ref="PRS1283Abre">
                     <roleName type="title">fitāwrāri</roleName></persName>
                   in <date>1699</date>
                  and then he was introduced into the circle revolving around the royal persons. 
                  He supported the coming to power of 
                  <persName ref="PRS5616IyasuI"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName>
                     ʾIyāsu the Great</persName>'s son 
                  <persName ref="PRS9152TaklaHa"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName>
                     Takla Hāymānot I</persName>. He openly conspired against 
                  <persName ref="PRS10473Yostos"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName>
                     Yosṭos</persName> in around <date>1712</date> and was imprisoned. </floruit>
          
               
